-------
This command is used to grab an image from the current
screen, and load it into the Bob bank. The command
must be followed by an image number to be loaded with
the grabbed image, and then the coordinates for the
corners of the rectangle that you want to make use of.


			-=- 156 -=-

For example, if you wanted to load a block of graphics
into Bob number 1, you could use:

                 Get Bob 1,Xl,Y1 To X2,Y2

You can select an optional screen number from which
