---------------
This command is used to load the whole colour palette
used for your Bobs into the current screen. A mask can
be added if you like, which will load a selection of these
colours only. Each individual colour is represented by
one "bit" of the mask set to a zero for OFF and a one for
ON. Colours run from right to left, so colour zero is
represented by the bit at the right-hand end of the mask,
colour 1is the second from the right, and so on. Supposing
