Changing a sample bank
----------------------
SAM BANK

Digital sound samples are normally stored in
memory bank 5, but you can assign a new memory
bank to hold your sound samples with the SAM
BANK command. Just include a bank number after
this instruction and all future SAM PLAY
commands will suck their sounds from that bank.
If you set up several parallel banks, Easy AMOS
can exploit their delights at any time with a simple
call such as:

Sam Bank 4

